{"timestamp":"2026-05-28T18:14:39.868Z","type":"tool","step":"IDLE","details":{"toolName":"task","args":{"description":"Implement compatibility fix","prompt":"You are an implementation subagent. Work in /Users/bbaaxx/AgentsPlayground/opencode-mdocs. Do write code. Do NOT commit.\n\nRequired skills/process: Follow TDD. First update tests to current opencode contract, run focused test and confirm it fails for the expected reason, then implement minimal code to pass.\n\nInitiative: fix-v1-opencode-compatibility — Fix v1 opencode Plugin Compatibility.\nObjective: Patch opencode-mdocs@1.0.0 compatibility with current opencode so first install visibly registers the bundled mdocs-orchestrator agent, exposes custom tools, and keeps skill registration deduplicated.\n\nRoot cause context:\n- Current src/plugin.ts registers agent under stale cfg.agents array.\n- Current opencode config uses cfg.agent object keyed by agent name.\n- Current src/plugin.ts exposes custom tools under stale tools.\n- Current opencode plugin hooks expose custom tools under singular tool.\n- src/__tests__/plugin.test.ts currently tests old shape and uses plugin.tools.\n- agents/mdocs-orchestrator.md has frontmatter and body prompt. Current config should inline the body as prompt and set metadata/permissions in cfg.agent['mdocs-orchestrator'].\n\nPlan tasks to execute now:\n1. Modify src/__tests__/plugin.test.ts:\n   - Import default plugin from ../index.\n   - Replace tool call sites from plugin.tools.* to plugin.tool.*.\n   - Replace cfg.agents assertions with cfg.agent['mdocs-orchestrator'] assertions.\n   - Assert description = 'Orchestrates work using the mdocs initiative/wiki workflow.'\n   - Assert mode = 'primary'.\n   - Assert permission equals { read:'allow', glob:'allow', grep:'allow', list:'allow', edit:'allow', write:'allow', bash:'allow' }.\n   - Assert prompt contains 'You are a workflow orchestrator using the mdocs system.'\n   - Assert cfg.agents is undefined in new-config cases.\n   - Add test that plugin.tool exposes mdocs_init, mdocs_status, mdocs_search, mdocs_dispatch, mdocs_audit and plugin.tools is undefined.\n   - Add default export smoke test: typeof pluginDefault === 'function'; await pluginDefault({client:{}, project:{}, directory:testDir}); returned hooks.tool.mdocs_status exists.\n2. Run: npm test -- src/__tests__/plugin.test.ts. Confirm RED due to plugin.tool/cfg.agent missing.\n3. Modify src/plugin.ts:\n   - Add helper loadAgentPrompt(agentPath) that reads file and strips YAML frontmatter.\n   - In config hook use cfg.agent ||= {}; if cfg.agent['mdocs-orchestrator'] absent, set object with description/mode/permission/prompt.\n   - Do not create cfg.agents for current opencode compatibility.\n   - Keep existing skill path registration and dedup behavior.\n   - Rename custom tools key from tools to tool.\n4. Run: npm test -- src/__tests__/plugin.test.ts. Confirm GREEN.\n\nReturn final message with:\n- status: DONE, DONE_WITH_CONCERNS, NEEDS_CONTEXT, or BLOCKED\n- files changed\n- exact RED test failure summary\n- exact GREEN verification output summary\n- any concerns.","subagent_type":"general","task_id":"","command":"execute fix-v1-opencode-compatibility tasks 1-2"}}}
