{"timestamp":"2026-05-29T17:29:13.781Z","type":"tool","step":"IDLE","details":{"toolName":"write","args":{"content":"# Fresh Agent Implementation Prompt: mdocs UX Improvements\n\n## Context\n\nYou are implementing three initiatives for the `opencode-mdocs` plugin. Work in `/Users/bbaaxx/AgentsPlayground/opencode-mdocs`. The repo is already cloned and dependencies installed (`npm install` was run).\n\n## Current State\n\n- **Version**: 1.0.2\n- **Tests**: 90/90 passing, `npm test` and `npm run build` both pass.\n- **Source files to know**:\n  - `src/plugin.ts` — exports `tool` object with `mdocs_init`, `mdocs_status`, `mdocs_search`, `mdocs_dispatch`, `mdocs_audit`. Custom tools go here.\n  - `src/initiative.ts` — InitiativeManager with `create()`, `read()`, `update()`, `findById()`, `findBlocked()`, `findOverdue()`. Filename derived from `slugify(title)` + `--created.md`.\n  - `src/wiki.ts` — WikiManager with `create()`, `read()`, `update()`, `delete()`.\n  - `src/types.ts` — Initiative, WikiEntry, PlanItem interfaces.\n  - `src/__tests__/plugin.test.ts` — plugin tests, all use `(plugin as any).tool.mdocs_xxx.execute(...)`.\n\n## Initiative Files (read these first)\n\nRead each initiative file to understand the goal before writing any code:\n- `mdocs/initiatives/fix-slug-initiative-ux--2026-05-29.md`\n- `mdocs/initiatives/add-mdocs-cli-commands--2026-05-29.md`\n- `mdocs/initiatives/add-initiatives-wiki-validation--2026-05-29.md`\n\n## Implementation Order\n\nDo them in this order: `fix-slug-initiative-ux` → `add-mdocs-cli-commands` → `add-initiatives-wiki-validation`.\n\n---\n\n## Initiative 1: fix-slug-initiative-ux\n\n### What's broken\n\n`formatFileName` in `src/initiative.ts` always uses `slugify(title)` as the filename stem, ignoring the `id` field. Example: initiative with `title: \"Install and Configure opencode-mdocs\"` gets filename `install-and-configure-opencode-mdocs--2026-05-27.md`, but frontmatter `id: install-mdocs`. When an agent tries to read using the `id` as filename stem (`install-mdocs--2026-05-27.md`), it fails.\n\nThe INDEX.md shows title + tags but NOT the actual filename, so agents can't discover it without guessing.\n\n### Required changes\n\n**File: `src/initiative.ts`**\n\n1. Modify `formatFileName()` to use `id` (slugified) as the filename stem when `id` is set and non-empty, falling back to `slugify(title)` otherwise:\n   ```typescript\n   private formatFileName(initiative: Initiative): string {\n     const stem = initiative.id ? this.slugify(initiative.id) : this.slugify(initiative.title);\n     return `${stem}--${initiative.created}.md`;\n   }\n   ```\n   - Note: `slugify('install-mdocs')` returns `install-mdocs` (no change needed since `id` is already slug-like).\n   - For a custom `id` like `my-custom-id`, slugify produces `my-custom-id`.\n   - This ensures `id` and filename stem are always consistent.\n\n2. Update `updateIndex()` in `src/initiative.ts` to include the actual filename in INDEX display:\n   ```typescript\n   const lines = initiatives.map(i => {\n     const fileName = `${this.slugify(i.id || i.title)}--${i.created}.md`;\n     return `- **${i.title}** (${fileName}) (${i.status}) — ${i.created} — [${i.tags.join(', ')}]`;\n   });\n   ```\n   Wait — for update, the filename uses `i.id` slugified if set. Make sure the INDEX shows the ACTUAL filename, which requires calling `formatFileName(i)` or reconstructing the stem properly. The cleanest way: use `this.formatFileName(i)` since it already has the logic:\n   ```typescript\n   const fileName = this.formatFileName(i);\n   return `- **${i.title}** (${fileName}) (${i.status}) — ${i.created} — [${i.tags.join(', ')}]`;\n   ```\n\n**File: `src/plugin.ts`**\n\n3. Add `mdocs_lookup` tool to `tool`:\n   ```typescript\n   mdocs_lookup: {\n     description: \"Look up an initiative by id, title, or slug and return its filename\",\n     execute: async (args: { query: string; field?: 'id' | 'title' | 'slug' }) => {\n       const q = (args.query || '').toLowerCase();\n       const initiativesDir = path.join(mdocsRoot, 'initiatives');\n       const files = fs.existsSync(initiativesDir)\n         ? fs.readdirSync(initiativesDir).filter(f => f.endsWith('.md') && f !== 'INDEX.md')\n         : [];\n       const results = [];\n       for (const f of files) {\n         try {\n           const init = initiatives.read(f);\n           if (!init) continue;\n           const matchId = init.id && init.id.toLowerCase() === q;\n           const matchTitle = init.title && init.title.toLowerCase().includes(q);\n           const matchSlug = this.slugify(init.title).includes(q) || this.slugify(init.id || '').includes(q);\n           const matchField = args.field === 'id' ? matchId\n             : args.field === 'title' ? matchTitle\n             : matchId || matchTitle || matchSlug;\n           if (!args.field && (matchId || matchTitle || matchSlug)) {\n             results.push({ filename: f, id: init.id, title: init.title, status: init.status, tags: init.tags });\n           } else if (matchField) {\n             results.push({ filename: f, id: init.id, title: init.title, status: init.status, tags: init.tags });\n           }\n         } catch { /* skip */ }\n       }\n       if (results.length === 0) return { error: 'No initiatives found for query', query: args.query };\n       return { results };\n     }\n   }\n   ```\n   Add a `slugify` helper in plugin.ts that matches the one in initiative.ts for consistency.\n\n**File: `src/__tests__/plugin.test.ts`**\n\n4. Add test for `mdocs_lookup`:\n   ```typescript\n   test('mdocs_lookup returns correct filename for id query', async () => {\n     const plugin = createPlugin(testDir);\n     (plugin as any).tool.mdocs_init.execute();\n     // Create initiative with custom id\n     const fs = require('fs');\n     const initDir = path.join(testDir, 'mdocs', 'initiatives');\n     fs.mkdirSync(initDir, { recursive: true });\n     fs.writeFileSync(path.join(initDir, 'install-and-configure-opencode-mdocs--2026-05-27.md'), `---\\nid: install-mdocs\\ntitle: Install and Configure opencode-mdocs\\nstatus: active\\ncreated: 2026-05-27\\nupdated: 2026-05-27\\nowner: test\\ntags: [setup, plugin]\\nrelated_wiki: []\\n---\\n\\n## Objective\\nTest\\n\\n## Plan\\n- [ ] Step 1\\n\\n## Progress Log\\n\\n## Artifacts\\n`);\n     const result = await (plugin as any).tool.mdocs_lookup.execute({ query: 'install-mdocs', field: 'id' });\n     expect(result.error).toBeUndefined();\n     expect(result.results[0].filename).toBe('install-and-configure-opencode-mdocs--2026-05-27.md');\n   });\n   ```\n\n5. Add test for INDEX showing filename:\n   ```typescript\n   test('INDEX displays actual filename', () => {\n     const plugin = createPlugin(testDir);\n     plugin.config({} as any);\n     const initDir = path.join(testDir, 'mdocs', 'initiatives');\n     const fs = require('fs');\n     fs.mkdirSync(initDir, { recursive: true });\n     fs.writeFileSync(path.join(initDir, 'install-and-configure-opencode-mdocs--2026-05-27.md'), `---\\nid: install-mdocs\\ntitle: Install and Configure opencode-mdocs\\nstatus: active\\ncreated: 2026-05-27\\nupdated: 2026-05-27\\nowner: test\\ntags: [setup, plugin]\\nrelated_wiki: []\\n---\\n\\n## Objective\\nTest\\n\\n## Plan\\n- [ ] Step 1\\n\\n## Progress Log\\n\\n## Artifacts\\n`);\n     const index = fs.readFileSync(path.join(initDir, 'INDEX.md'), 'utf8');\n     expect(index).toContain('install-and-configure-opencode-mdocs--2026-05-27.md');\n     expect(index).toContain('**Install and Configure opencode-mdocs**');\n   });\n   ```\n\n---\n\n## Initiative 2: add-mdocs-cli-commands\n\n### What's broken\n\nAgents had to manually create/edit files, edit INDEX.md, and use grep for searching. No programmatic API for initiative/wiki CRUD.\n\n### Required changes\n\nAdd a `mdocs` tool with subcommands to `src/plugin.ts`:\n\n```typescript\nmdocs: {\n  description: \"Run mdocs commands: initiative.create, initiative.update, initiative.done, wiki.create, validate, index.sync\",\n  execute: async (args: { command: string; args: any }) => {\n    const { command, args: cmdArgs } = args;\n    switch (command) {\n      case 'initiative.create':\n        return cmdArgs.title\n          ? (() => {\n              const id = cmdArgs.id || cmdArgs.title;\n              const created = new Date().toISOString().split('T')[0];\n              const initiative = {\n                id,\n                title: cmdArgs.title,\n                status: 'active',\n                created,\n                updated: created,\n                owner: cmdArgs.owner || 'agent',\n                tags: cmdArgs.tags || [],\n                relatedWiki: cmdArgs.relatedWiki || [],\n                objective: cmdArgs.objective || '',\n                plan: (cmdArgs.plan || []).map((d: string) => ({ description: d, status: 'pending' as const })),\n                progressLog: [`Initiative created by mdocs CLI`],\n                artifacts: []\n              };\n              const filePath = initiatives.create(initiative);\n              return { success: true, filename: filePath, id };\n            })()\n          : { error: 'title is required for initiative.create' };\n      case 'initiative.update':\n        return cmdArgs.id\n          ? (() => {\n              const init = initiatives.findById(cmdArgs.id);\n              if (!init) return { error: `Initiative not found: ${cmdArgs.id}` };\n              const allowedUpdates = ['status', 'tags', 'priority', 'dueDate', 'dependsOn', 'owner'];\n              allowedUpdates.forEach((field: string) => {\n                if (cmdArgs[field] !== undefined) (init as any)[field] = cmdArgs[field];\n              });\n              init.updated = new Date().toISOString().split('T')[0];\n              if (cmdArgs.progressNote) init.progressLog.push(cmdArgs.progressNote);\n              initiatives.update(`${initiatives as any}.dir/${init.id}--${init.created}.md`.replace('\\\\', '/'), init);\n              return { success: true, id: init.id };\n            })()\n          : { error: 'id is required for initiative.update' };\n      case 'initiative.done':\n        return cmdArgs.id\n          ? (() => {\n              const init = initiatives.findById(cmdArgs.id);\n              if (!init) return { error: `Initiative not found: ${cmdArgs.id}` };\n              init.status = 'done';\n              init.updated = new Date().toISOString().split('T')[0];\n              init.progressLog.push(`[${new Date().toISOString()}] Marked as done via mdocs CLI`);\n              const fileName = `${init.id}--${init.created}.md`;\n              initiatives.update(fileName, init);\n              return { success: true, id: init.id };\n            })()\n          : { error: 'id is required for initiative.done' };\n      case 'wiki.create':\n        return cmdArgs.category && cmdArgs.id && cmdArgs.title\n          ? (() => {\n              const created = new Date().toISOString().split('T')[0];\n              wiki.create({\n                id: cmdArgs.id,\n                title: cmdArgs.title,\n                category: cmdArgs.category,\n                content: cmdArgs.content || '',\n                created,\n                updated: created,\n                relatedInitiatives: cmdArgs.relatedInitiatives || [],\n                tags: cmdArgs.tags || []\n              });\n              return { success: true, category: cmdArgs.category, id: cmdArgs.id };\n            })()\n          : { error: 'category, id, and title are required for wiki.create' };\n      case 'validate':\n        return { error: 'validate not yet implemented' }; // covered by initiative 3\n      case 'index.sync':\n        return { error: 'index.sync not yet implemented' }; // covered by initiative 3\n      default:\n        return { error: `Unknown command: ${command}. Supported: initiative.create, initiative.update, initiative.done, wiki.create` };\n    }\n  }\n}\n```\n\nWait — the `initiative.update` and `initiative.done` use `update()` which takes a filename, not an id. Fix that to derive the correct filename. The `InitiativeManager` has `findById()` but `update()` takes a `fileName`. Use `formatFileName(init)` to get the right filename.\n\nAlso, `updateIndex()` is called inside `create()` and `update()`, so INDEX auto-syncs automatically — no separate `index.sync` needed except as a force-regenerate option.\n\nAdd tests for the `mdocs` tool commands in `src/__tests__/plugin.test.ts`.\n\n---\n\n## Initiative 3: add-initiatives-wiki-validation\n\n### What's broken\n\nNo validation: duplicate IDs can be created, required fields aren't checked, `related_wiki` references can point to non-existent wiki entries, and INDEX consistency is never checked.\n\n### Required changes\n\n**File: `src/initiative.ts`**\n\nAdd validation method to InitiativeManager:\n\n```typescript\nvalidate(): { valid: boolean; errors: string[]; warnings: string[] } {\n  const errors: string[] = [];\n  const warnings: string[] = [];\n  const all = this.listAll();\n  const ids = all.map(i => i.id);\n\n  // Check for duplicate IDs\n  const seenIds = new Set<string>();\n  for (const init of all) {\n    if (!init.id) errors.push(`Missing id in initiative`);\n    else {\n      if (seenIds.has(init.id)) errors.push(`Duplicate id: ${init.id}`);\n      seenIds.add(init.id);\n    }\n  }\n\n  // Check required fields\n  for (const init of all) {\n    if (!init.title) errors.push(`Missing title in initiative: ${init.id}`);\n    if (!init.status) errors.push(`Missing status in initiative: ${init.id}`);\n    if (!init.created) errors.push(`Missing created in initiative: ${init.id}`);\n  }\n\n  // Check related_wiki references\n  for (const init of all) {\n    for (const ref of init.relatedWiki) {\n      const [cat, id] = ref.split('/');\n      if (cat && id) {\n        const wikiPath = path.join(this.dir, '..', 'wiki', cat, `${id}.md`);\n        if (!fs.existsSync(wikiPath)) {\n          warnings.push(`related_wiki \"${ref}\" not found for initiative: ${init.id}`);\n        }\n      }\n    }\n  }\n\n  return { valid: errors.length === 0, errors, warnings };\n}\n```\n\nAdd to WikiManager too:\n\n```typescript\nvalidate(): { valid: boolean; errors: string[]; warnings: string[] } {\n  const errors: string[] = [];\n  const warnings: string[] = [];\n  const categories = fs.existsSync(this.dir) ? fs.readdirSync(this.dir) : [];\n  const allEntries: WikiEntry[] = [];\n  for (const cat of categories) {\n    const catDir = path.join(this.dir, cat);\n    if (!fs.statSync(catDir).isDirectory()) continue;\n    const files = fs.readdirSync(catDir).filter(f => f.endsWith('.md') && f !== 'INDEX.md');\n    for (const f of files) {\n      try {\n        const entry = this.read(cat, f.replace('.md', ''));\n        if (entry) allEntries.push(entry);\n      } catch { /* skip */ }\n    }\n  }\n\n  for (const entry of allEntries) {\n    if (!entry.id) errors.push(`Missing id in wiki entry`);\n    if (!entry.title) errors.push(`Missing title in wiki entry: ${entry.id}`);\n    if (!entry.category) errors.push(`Missing category in wiki entry: ${entry.id}`);\n  }\n\n  return { valid: errors.length === 0, errors, warnings };\n}\n```\n\nAdd `mdocs_validate` tool to `src/plugin.ts`:\n\n```typescript\nmdocs_validate: {\n  description: \"Validate all initiatives and wiki entries: duplicate IDs, required fields, broken related_wiki references, orphaned entries\",\n  execute: async () => {\n    const initResult = initiatives.validate();\n    const wikiResult = wiki.validate();\n    return {\n      initiatives: initResult,\n      wiki: wikiResult,\n      valid: initResult.valid && wikiResult.valid\n    };\n  }\n}\n```\n\nAdd tests for validation in `src/__tests__/plugin.test.ts`.\n\n---\n\n## Verification After Each Initiative\n\nAfter implementing each initiative:\n1. `npm test` — all tests must pass\n2. `npm run build` — TypeScript must compile cleanly\n3. Update the initiative's Progress Log with what was done and verified\n\n## Important Rules\n\n- Use TDD: write failing test first, then minimal code to pass.\n- Do NOT modify existing passing tests unless the test itself was testing the OLD (broken) behavior.\n- Commit after each initiative is complete: one commit per initiative with a descriptive message.\n- After all three are done, run `npm test` and `npm run build` one final time to confirm everything passes.","filePath":"/Users/bbaaxx/AgentsPlayground/opencode-mdocs/docs/fresh-agent-implementation-prompt.md"}}}
