{"timestamp":"2026-05-29T17:36:26.975Z","type":"tool","step":"IDLE","details":{"toolName":"apply_patch","args":{"patchText":"*** Begin Patch\n*** Add File: docs/superpowers/plans/2026-05-29-v102-testing-round-fixes.md\n+# v1.0.2 Testing Round Fixes Implementation Plan\n+\n+> **For agentic workers:** REQUIRED SUB-SKILL: Use superpowers:subagent-driven-development (recommended) or superpowers:executing-plans to implement this plan task-by-task. Steps use checkbox (`- [ ]`) syntax for tracking.\n+\n+**Goal:** Implement the three active mdocs UX/integrity initiatives from `docs/fresh-agent-implementation-prompt.md` with TDD, verification, and one commit per initiative.\n+\n+**Architecture:** Keep changes inside existing manager/tool boundaries. `InitiativeManager` owns initiative filename/index/validation behavior, `WikiManager` owns wiki validation, and `createPlugin().tool` exposes user-facing custom tools. Tests live in `src/__tests__/plugin.test.ts` plus targeted manager tests if needed.\n+\n+**Tech Stack:** TypeScript, Node.js `fs/path`, Jest, existing opencode plugin tool shape.\n+\n+---\n+\n+## File Structure\n+\n+- Modify `src/initiative.ts`: id-based filename stems, public filename lookup helper if needed, duplicate/required/reference validation, index filename display.\n+- Modify `src/wiki.ts`: wiki entry validation.\n+- Modify `src/plugin.ts`: add `slugify`, `mdocs_lookup`, `mdocs`, and `mdocs_validate`; optionally include validation in `mdocs_status`.\n+- Modify `src/__tests__/plugin.test.ts`: failing tests for each new tool and regression.\n+- Update `mdocs/initiatives/*.md`: progress logs after each initiative verification.\n+\n+## Task 1: Fix slug/filename UX\n+\n+**Files:**\n+- Modify: `src/__tests__/plugin.test.ts`\n+- Modify: `src/initiative.ts`\n+- Modify: `src/plugin.ts`\n+- Update: `mdocs/initiatives/fix-slug-initiative-ux--2026-05-29.md`\n+\n+- [ ] Write failing tests for `mdocs_lookup`, id-based create filenames, and INDEX filename display.\n+- [ ] Run focused test command and confirm failures are due to missing behavior: `npm test -- src/__tests__/plugin.test.ts`.\n+- [ ] Implement `InitiativeManager.formatFileName()` to prefer non-empty `id` slug over `title` slug.\n+- [ ] Implement INDEX lines using actual `formatFileName(i)`.\n+- [ ] Add plugin-level slug helper and `mdocs_lookup` tool that searches id, title, and id/title/filename slugs and returns actual existing filenames.\n+- [ ] Run `npm test -- src/__tests__/plugin.test.ts`, then `npm test`, then `npm run build`.\n+- [ ] Append progress log with tests/build evidence.\n+- [ ] Commit only relevant files with message like `fix: improve initiative filename lookup`.\n+\n+## Task 2: Add mdocs command tool\n+\n+**Files:**\n+- Modify: `src/__tests__/plugin.test.ts`\n+- Modify: `src/plugin.ts`\n+- Update: `mdocs/initiatives/add-mdocs-cli-commands--2026-05-29.md`\n+\n+- [ ] Write failing tests for `mdocs` commands: `initiative.create`, `initiative.update`, `initiative.done`, `wiki.create`, plus unknown/missing required args.\n+- [ ] Run focused test command and confirm failures are due to missing `mdocs` tool/commands.\n+- [ ] Implement `mdocs` command switch using existing managers.\n+- [ ] For initiative update/done, derive the correct filename from the found initiative via the same id-based convention instead of guessing title stems.\n+- [ ] Return structured success/error objects without throwing for user input errors.\n+- [ ] Run focused tests, full `npm test`, and `npm run build`.\n+- [ ] Append progress log with tests/build evidence.\n+- [ ] Commit only relevant files with message like `feat: add mdocs command tool`.\n+\n+## Task 3: Add initiatives/wiki validation\n+\n+**Files:**\n+- Modify: `src/__tests__/plugin.test.ts`\n+- Modify: `src/initiative.ts`\n+- Modify: `src/wiki.ts`\n+- Modify: `src/plugin.ts`\n+- Update: `mdocs/initiatives/add-initiatives-wiki-validation--2026-05-29.md`\n+\n+- [ ] Write failing tests for duplicate initiative IDs, missing required initiative fields, broken `related_wiki`, missing wiki fields, and `mdocs_validate` aggregation.\n+- [ ] Run focused tests and confirm expected failures.\n+- [ ] Implement `InitiativeManager.validate()` returning `{ valid, errors, warnings }`.\n+- [ ] Add duplicate-id checks to `create()` and `update()` so invalid writes fail before corrupting state.\n+- [ ] Implement `WikiManager.validate()` returning `{ valid, errors, warnings }`.\n+- [ ] Add `mdocs_validate` tool and wire `mdocs` command `validate` to the same result.\n+- [ ] Optionally include validation in `mdocs_status` to satisfy the initiative acceptance criterion.\n+- [ ] Run focused tests, full `npm test`, and `npm run build`.\n+- [ ] Append progress log with tests/build evidence.\n+- [ ] Commit only relevant files with message like `feat: validate mdocs integrity`.\n+\n+## Final Verification\n+\n+- [ ] Run `npm test` and confirm all Jest tests pass.\n+- [ ] Run `npm run build` and confirm TypeScript compiles.\n+- [ ] Inspect `git status --short`, `git diff`, and `git log --oneline -10` before final report.\n+- [ ] Offer to mark initiatives done after review/integration.\n+\n+## Self-Review\n+\n+- Spec coverage: all three initiatives map to Tasks 1-3.\n+- Placeholder scan: no TBD/TODO placeholders remain.\n+- Type consistency: plan uses existing `Initiative`, `WikiEntry`, and plugin tool conventions.\n*** End Patch"}}}
{"timestamp":"2026-05-29T17:36:29.715Z","type":"tool","step":"IDLE","details":{"toolName":"write","args":{"content":"---\nid: add-wiki-bidirectional-links\ntitle: Add Bidirectional Wiki-Initiative Links and Back-Link Generation\nstatus: active\npriority: medium\ncreated: 2026-05-29\nupdated: 2026-05-29\nowner: bbaaxx\ntags: [enhancement, wiki, links, back-reference, cross-reference]\nrelated_wiki: []\n---\n\n## Objective\n\nAdd automatic back-link generation so wiki entries list all initiatives that reference them via `related_wiki`, and add a `mdocs wiki.link` command to establish bidirectional links programmatically.\n\n## Context\n\n- Agent feedback: \"No bidirectional links — Initiative can link to wiki, but wiki doesn't auto-list related initiatives. Had to manually add note to testing-results.md.\"\n- Also: \"No wiki-to-wiki linking — If wiki entry A references wiki entry B, no automatic cross-reference.\"\n- Currently wiki entries have `related_initiatives` in frontmatter but no automatic generation of a \"Referenced by:\" section in the wiki body.\n\n## Plan\n\n- [ ] Add `addRelatedInitiative()` method to WikiManager\n  - Reads existing `related_initiatives` array from frontmatter\n  - Adds initiative id if not already present (no duplicates)\n  - Updates frontmatter `related_initiatives`\n  - Updates `updated` timestamp\n- [ ] Add `getReferencedBy()` method to WikiManager\n  - Scans all initiatives for `related_wiki` entries matching this wiki entry\n  - Returns list of initiative ids that reference this wiki\n- [ ] Modify wiki.create and wiki.update to auto-add back-link in wiki content\n  - After creating/updating, append to wiki entry body a section:\n    `## Referenced By\\n- initiative-id-1\\n- initiative-id-2\\n`\n  - Only append if not already present (deduplicated)\n- [ ] Add `wiki.link` command to `mdocs` tool\n  - Args: `{ initiativeId: string, wikiSlug: string }`\n  - Adds `related_wiki: [wikiSlug]` to initiative\n  - Calls `addRelatedInitiative()` on wiki entry\n  - Returns `{ success: true, bidirectional: true }`\n- [ ] Add wiki-to-wiki cross-reference support\n  - In wiki entries, detect references like `[[category/id]]` or `[id](category/id)` in body\n  - Auto-add to `related_wiki` of the referenced entry (bidirectional)\n  - Add `wiki.xref` command to manually create cross-references\n- [ ] Add tests for bidirectional link generation and wiki.link command\n- [ ] Update mdocs-workflow skill to document bidirectional linking\n\n## Acceptance Criteria\n\n- When `mdocs { command: 'wiki.link', args: { initiativeId: 'foo', wikiSlug: 'testing/results' } }` is called:\n  - Initiative's `related_wiki` includes `testing/results`\n  - Wiki entry's `related_initiatives` includes `foo`\n  - Both frontmatter files are updated atomically\n- Wiki entry body contains auto-generated \"Referenced By\" section listing all linking initiatives.\n- All existing tests pass; new tests for bidirectional links.\n\n## Progress Log\n- [2026-05-29] Created initiative from wiki integration feedback: no bidirectional links, manual back-link addition required.\n- [2026-05-29] Will implement after INITIATIVE 2 (add-mdocs-cli-commands) is complete.\n\n## Artifacts\n- `mdocs/initiatives/add-wiki-bidirectional-links--2026-05-29.md` — this initiative","filePath":"/Users/bbaaxx/AgentsPlayground/opencode-mdocs/mdocs/initiatives/add-wiki-bidirectional-links--2026-05-29.md"}}}
