{"timestamp":"2026-05-29T17:41:51.549Z","type":"tool","step":"IDLE","details":{"toolName":"task","args":{"description":"Implement slug lookup","prompt":"You are implementing Task 1 of docs/superpowers/plans/2026-05-29-v102-testing-round-fixes.md on branch v1.0.2-testing-round-fixes in /Users/bbaaxx/AgentsPlayground/opencode-mdocs.\n\nUse TDD strictly: write failing tests first, run them and confirm RED, then implement minimal code, then verify GREEN. Do not touch unrelated preexisting dirty files except where necessary. There are preexisting dirty/untracked mdocs docs and src/plugin.ts changes; preserve them. Stage only files relevant to this task when committing.\n\nInitiative objective (fix-slug-initiative-ux): Fix slug/id mismatch, show actual filename in initiatives INDEX, and add mdocs_lookup resolving id/title/slug to actual filename.\n\nCurrent plan for this task:\n- Write failing tests for mdocs_lookup, id-based create filenames, and INDEX filename display.\n- Run focused test command and confirm failures are due to missing behavior: npm test -- src/__tests__/plugin.test.ts.\n- Implement InitiativeManager.formatFileName() to prefer non-empty id slug over title slug.\n- Implement INDEX lines using actual formatFileName(i).\n- Add plugin-level slug helper and mdocs_lookup tool that searches id, title, and id/title/filename slugs and returns actual existing filenames.\n- Run npm test -- src/__tests__/plugin.test.ts, then npm test, then npm run build.\n- Append progress log with tests/build evidence in mdocs/initiatives/fix-slug-initiative-ux--2026-05-29.md.\n- Commit only relevant files with message: fix: improve initiative filename lookup.\n\nRelevant existing files:\n- src/initiative.ts currently formatFileName uses slugify(title), updateIndex omits filename.\n- src/plugin.ts currently tools are mdocs_init, mdocs_status, mdocs_search, mdocs_dispatch, mdocs_audit. It has preexisting robustness changes; keep them.\n- src/__tests__/plugin.test.ts has a config test expecting exactly the old tool list; update only as required to include mdocs_lookup.\n\nAcceptance criteria:\n- createPlugin(directory).tool.mdocs_lookup.execute({ query: 'install-mdocs', field: 'id' }) is callable and returns actual existing filename.\n- Lookup by title works.\n- Creating an initiative with custom id uses id stem for filename.\n- INDEX.md displays actual filename.\n- Focused and full tests pass, build passes.\n\nBefore committing, inspect git status, git diff, and git log --oneline -10; stage only task-relevant files (likely src/initiative.ts, src/plugin.ts, src/__tests__/plugin.test.ts, mdocs/initiatives/fix-slug-initiative-ux--2026-05-29.md, maybe generated mdocs/initiatives/INDEX.md if changed by this task). Do not stage unrelated docs/wiki changes or other initiative files.\n\nReturn one final message with status DONE/DONE_WITH_CONCERNS/BLOCKED, summary of changes, RED/GREEN verification commands and outcomes, commit SHA if committed, and any concerns.","subagent_type":"general","task_id":"","command":"implement task 1 slug lookup"}}}
