{"timestamp":"2026-05-29T17:59:39.820Z","type":"tool","step":"IDLE","details":{"toolName":"task","args":{"description":"Implement mdocs CLI","prompt":"Implement Task 2 of docs/superpowers/plans/2026-05-29-v102-testing-round-fixes.md on branch v1.0.2-testing-round-fixes in /Users/bbaaxx/AgentsPlayground/opencode-mdocs.\n\nUse TDD strictly: write failing tests first, run and confirm RED, implement minimal code, verify GREEN. Preserve unrelated preexisting dirty/untracked files unless directly relevant. Stage only task-relevant files when committing.\n\nInitiative objective (add-mdocs-cli-commands): Add a `mdocs` custom tool with subcommands so agents can perform initiative/wiki operations without manual file manipulation.\n\nImplement scope:\n- Add `mdocs` tool in `src/plugin.ts` with description and execute(args: { command: string; args: any }).\n- Commands:\n  - `initiative.create`: requires title; optional id, owner, tags, relatedWiki, objective, plan. Creates active initiative with dates, plan items pending, progressLog includes creation note. Return `{ success: true, filename, id }` where filename is basename or path as tests define clearly.\n  - `initiative.update`: requires id. Finds by id. Allows updates to status, tags, priority, dueDate, dependsOn, owner. Updates date. Appends progressNote when provided. Uses correct existing filename/id-based filename when calling manager.update.\n  - `initiative.done`: requires id. Finds by id. Sets status done, updated date, appends done log, updates correct filename.\n  - `wiki.create`: requires category, id, title. Creates wiki entry with dates, content, relatedInitiatives, tags. Return structured success.\n  - `validate`: for now may return `{ error: 'validate not yet implemented' }` if mdocs_validate not present yet; Task 3 will complete.\n  - `index.sync`: may return `{ error: 'index.sync not yet implemented' }` unless simple safe implementation exists.\n  - unknown command returns helpful error listing supported commands.\n- Update config hook tool list test to include `mdocs`.\n- Add tests in `src/__tests__/plugin.test.ts` for create/update/done/wiki.create and error cases.\n- Update `mdocs/initiatives/add-mdocs-cli-commands--2026-05-29.md` progress log with RED/GREEN evidence. This file is currently untracked but relevant; include it in commit if needed.\n\nImportant implementation detail:\n- InitiativeManager.update(fileName, init) takes a filename, not id. Derive the correct filename. If the manager has a public helper from Task 1, use it; otherwise carefully match id-stem convention or locate existing filename through lookup/read files.\n\nVerification:\n- RED: `npm test -- src/__tests__/plugin.test.ts` failing for missing `mdocs` behavior.\n- GREEN: `npm test -- src/__tests__/plugin.test.ts`, `npm test`, `npm run build` pass.\n- Before commit, inspect status/diff/log; commit task changes with message `feat: add mdocs command tool`.\n\nReturn DONE/DONE_WITH_CONCERNS/BLOCKED with summary, RED/GREEN outputs, commit SHA, concerns.","subagent_type":"general","task_id":"","command":"implement task 2 mdocs CLI"}}}
