e INDEX ✓/✗\n- `index.sync` regenerates all INDEX files ✓/✗\n- `wiki.delete` with `{ category, id }` removes entry and updates indices ✓/✗\n- `wiki.list` with `{ category? }` returns entries filtered by category or all ✓/✗\n- All existing tests pass; new tests for each command ✓/✗\n\n### Review checklist\n- [ ] Command argument validation (missing id, missing category, etc.)\n- [ ] Error handling for not-found cases\n- [ ] Archive rejects non-done initiatives\n- [ ] INDEX regeneration is correct for both initiatives and wiki\n- [ ] Archive INDEX is created and maintained correctly\n- [ ] No security issues (path traversal, unsanitized input)\n- [ ] Tests cover success paths AND error paths\n- [ ] Existing tests were preserved (not broken)\n- [ ] Code follows existing patterns and conventions\n- [ ] No dead code or unused imports\n\nReturn your review as:\n```\nREVIEW: PASS or FAIL\nBLOCKING ISSUES: [list or \"none\"]\nMINOR OBSERVATIONS: [list or \"none\"]\nEVIDENCE INSPECTED: [list files and specific code reviewed]\n```","subagent_type":"general"}}}
