{"timestamp":"2026-05-31T22:49:42.510Z","type":"tool","step":"IDLE","details":{"toolName":"apply_patch","args":{"patchText":"*** Begin Patch\n*** Add File: mdocs/initiatives/fix-mdocs-first-activation-hook-error--2026-05-31.md\n+---\n+id: fix-mdocs-first-activation-hook-error\n+title: Fix mdocs First Activation Hook Error\n+status: active\n+created: 2026-05-31\n+updated: 2026-05-31\n+owner: system\n+tags: [bug, plugin, hooks, tools, orchestrator, activation]\n+related_wiki: []\n+phase: discovery\n+handoff_summary: \"First observed failure: invoking mdocs_status at start of an Mdocs-Orchestrator task displays `undefined is not an object (evaluating 'p.split')`. The generic `mdocs` command tool also appears to fail with the same error.\"\n+open_questions:\n+  - \"Is the failure caused by an opencode hook, the mdocs custom tool wrapper, path handling, or tool argument serialization?\"\n+  - \"Does the error happen only on first activation or on every invocation of affected tools?\"\n+blockers: []\n+next_action: \"Reproduce the first-activation error, trace the source of `p.split`, and patch the failing hook/tool path handling.\"\n+---\n+\n+## Objective\n+Find and fix the error that appears on first activation of an Mdocs-Orchestrator task, likely from a hook or custom tool invocation. The observed UI error is:\n+\n+```text\n+mdocs_status\n+undefined is not an object (evaluating 'p.split')\n+```\n+\n+During creation of this initiative, invoking the generic `mdocs` command tool also returned the same error, suggesting the issue may affect multiple mdocs custom tool entrypoints rather than only `mdocs_status`.\n+\n+## Plan\n+- [ ] Reproduce the failure with `mdocs_status` and the generic `mdocs` command tool in the local opencode-mdocs environment.\n+- [ ] Search source, generated `dist/`, plugin registration, and hook/config code for path splitting and custom tool argument handling that could call `.split` on `undefined`.\n+- [ ] Identify whether the root cause is hook activation, custom tool schema/wrapper behavior, working-directory discovery, or missing argument defaults.\n+- [ ] Add or update regression tests for the failing first-activation/custom-tool path.\n+- [ ] Implement the fix in source and rebuild generated artifacts if this repo requires committed build output.\n+- [ ] Verify `mdocs_status`, generic `mdocs` commands, and normal initiative discovery work without the `p.split` error.\n+- [ ] Document durable learning in a related wiki entry if the root cause is non-obvious.\n+\n+## Progress Log\n+- [2026-05-31] Created initiative from user report and screenshot. Initial evidence: `mdocs_status` failed with `undefined is not an object (evaluating 'p.split')`; fallback direct read of `mdocs/initiatives/INDEX.md` succeeded. Attempt to call the generic `mdocs` command tool also failed with the same error.\n+\n+## Artifacts\n+- User screenshot showing first observed `mdocs_status` failure.\n*** Update File: mdocs/initiatives/INDEX.md\n@@\n - **Add Wiki Stub Generation and Auto-Create from Initiative Links** (active) — 2026-05-29 — [enhancement, wiki, stub, auto-create, templates]\n+- **Fix mdocs First Activation Hook Error** (active) — 2026-05-31 — [bug, plugin, hooks, tools, orchestrator, activation]\n - **Fix v1 opencode Plugin Compatibility** (done) — 2026-05-28 — [bug, compatibility, v1, plugin, config, agent, tools]\n*** End Patch"}}}
