{"timestamp":"2026-05-31T23:36:46.021Z","type":"tool","initiativeId":"prepare-v1-1-0-release","step":"IDLE","details":{"toolName":"task","args":{"description":"Audit release readiness","prompt":"We are preparing opencode-mdocs for v1.1.0 release.\n\nInitiative objective:\nPrepare the repository for a v1.1.0 release by reviewing current changes, validating package metadata and docs, running verification, and producing release notes/readiness status.\n\nInitiative plan:\n1. Review prior v1 release initiative and current repo state for release process expectations.\n2. Inspect package metadata, changelog/release notes, README/docs, and version references for v1.1.0 readiness.\n3. Run relevant tests, lint/typecheck/build checks and mdocs validation.\n4. Update release artifacts and docs as needed.\n5. Summarize release readiness, blockers, and next steps for tagging/publishing.\n\nAssembled context from mdocs includes retrieved memory: original implementation plan, philosophy alignment roadmap, origin narrative, and prior first-activation-hook initiative. Current new initiative has no related wiki yet.\n\nYour task: Research/audit only; do not edit files. Inspect the repo for release process, package metadata, changelog/release notes, version references, tests/build scripts, and current git state. Also inspect the prior done initiative `prepare-v1-release--2026-05-27.md` if accessible. Return:\n- current package/version/package manager\n- release-related files found\n- recommended v1.1.0 file edits\n- exact verification commands to run\n- blockers/risks\n- concise release prep checklist\n\nVerification criteria: findings must cite file paths and concrete commands.","subagent_type":"general","task_id":"","command":"mdocs release audit"}}}
