{"timestamp":"2026-06-01T07:34:08.670Z","type":"tool","initiativeId":"add-opencode-mdocs-to-opencode-ecosystem","step":"IDLE","details":{"toolName":"mdocs","args":{"command":"initiative.create","args":{"title":"Clean Up Graph Validation Warnings","id":"clean-up-graph-warnings","owner":"bbaaxx","tags":"[cleanup, validation, graph, links, housekeeping]","priority":"medium","Resolve all warnings emitted by mdocs_validate under the GRAPH result so the cross-link graph linter passes cleanly. Specific issues to fix: (a) 26 done initiatives have no stable wiki learning linked; (b) 5 wiki entries are missing backlinks to specific initiatives; (c) 10 wiki entries are not referenced by any initiative. Result must be that mdocs_validate emits zero graph warnings while preserving all existing semantic content.":"","plan":"- [ ] Inventory current graph warnings\n  - [x] Run `mdocs_validate` and capture exact warning list\n  - [x] Read linter rules in `src/linter.ts` (lines 100-175) to confirm semantics\n  - [x] Read all 26 done initiative frontmatter and 10+ wiki frontmatter\n- [ ] Group A — add stable wiki refs to done initiatives\n  - [ ] For each done initiative with empty or non-stable `related_wiki`, pick a stable wiki entry that semantically fits (or create a new stable wiki entry, or promote an existing wiki entry's lifecycle to `stable`)\n  - [ ] Update the initiative frontmatter\n  - [ ] When creating or promoting a wiki entry, also set `lifecycle: stable` plus v2 metadata\n- [ ] Group B — add missing wiki backlinks\n  - [ ] For each of the 5 specific missing-backlink warnings, add the initiative id to the wiki entry's `related_initiatives` array\n- [ ] Group C — link orphan wiki entries from at least one initiative\n  - [ ] For each of the 10 orphan wiki entries, find a done or active initiative that should reference it and update that initiative's `related_wiki`\n  - [ ] Where the wiki entry is the natural artifact of a single initiative, point the initiative at it; otherwise pick the most relevant\n- [ ] Verify\n  - [ ] Run `mdocs_validate` and confirm zero graph warnings remain\n  - [ ] Run `npm test` and `npm run build` to ensure no regressions\n- [ ] Report\n  - [ ] Update this initiative progress log with summary of changes\n  - [ ] Note any judgment calls (e.g., wiki entries promoted to stable) in the progress log"}}}}
