{"timestamp":"2026-06-01T07:53:21.106Z","type":"tool","initiativeId":"add-opencode-mdocs-to-opencode-ecosystem","step":"IDLE","details":{"toolName":"task","args":{"description":"Fix graph linter warnings","prompt":"You are fixing graph linter warnings in a project that uses the mdocs (memory docs) system. The repo is at `/Users/bbaaxx/AgentsPlayground/opencode-mdocs`. An active initiative `clean-up-graph-warnings` exists; read it first with `mdocs_lookup` to confirm.\n\n## Your Mission\nMake `mdocs_validate` emit zero graph warnings by:\n1. Linking 26 done initiatives to at least one stable (lifecycle: stable) wiki entry via `related_wiki`.\n2. Adding 5 missing backlinks from wiki entries to the initiatives that reference them via `related_initiatives`.\n3. Linking 10 orphan wiki entries (not referenced by any initiative) from at least one initiative each.\n\nYou must NOT change the linter, the tests, or any TypeScript code. Only edit markdown frontmatter in `mdocs/initiatives/*.md` and `mdocs/wiki/<category>/*.md`.\n\n## Linter Semantics (read `src/linter.ts` lines 100-175 if you need detail)\n- A done initiative must have at least one `related_wiki` entry whose target wiki file has `lifecycle: stable`. Otherwise warn: \"Done initiative <id> has no stable wiki learning\".\n- For every entry in a wiki entry's `related_initiatives`, an issue is raised if no initiative has that id, and vice versa for missing reciprocal links. So: an initiative in wiki's `related_initiatives` with no `related_wiki` to that wiki in some initiative's `related_wiki` is a problem only if it points to a missing initiative.\n- Backlink warning: \"Wiki <cat>/<id> missing backlink to initiative <init-id>\" fires when initiative I has `related_wiki: [<cat>/<id>]` but the wiki entry's `related_initiatives` does NOT include I's id. Fix: add the initiative id to the wiki entry's `related_initiatives` array.\n- Orphan warning: wiki entry not referenced by any initiative's `related_wiki`. Fix: add the wiki slug (e.g. `architecture/foo`) to some initiative's `related_wiki` array.\n\n## Current State of the Repo\n\n### Stable wiki entries (already lifecycle: stable)\n- `research/opencode-ecosystem-pr-submission`\n- `release/v1-1-0-readiness`\n- `developer/opencode-custom-tool-result-contract`\n- `roadmap/philosophy-alignment-roadmap`\n- `architecture/philosophy-implementation-gap-analysis`\n\n### Stable-like wiki entries (lifecycle: draft or missing) — candidates to promote to stable\n- `architecture/implementation-plan` (no lifecycle) — historical blueprint\n- `architecture/plugin-design-spec` (no lifecycle) — historical blueprint\n- `architecture/mdocs-tool-gates` (no lifecycle) — workflow design rule\n- `decisions/opencode-tool-registration` (no lifecycle) — fix pattern\n- `developer/agent-implementation-guide` (no lifecycle) — handoff doc\n- `philosophy/origin-narrative` (no lifecycle) — foundational narrative\n- `philosophy/core-principles` (no lifecycle) — foundational principles\n\nPromote these to `lifecycle: stable` if they capture durable knowledge that future agents/agents-onboarding will need. These are historical/architectural/principle docs, not transient, so they qualify.\n\n### 26 done initiatives with no stable wiki (id : current `related_wiki`)\n1. `complete-mdocs-cli-commands` : [] \n2. `fix-frontmatter-type-mismatch` : []\n3. `install-mdocs` : []\n4. `remove-default-model` : []\n5. `fix-slug-initiative-ux` : []\n6. `add-full-text-search` : []\n7. `fix-local-dogfooding-agent-discovery` : []\n8. `add-mdocs-linter-for-handoff-quality` : []\n9. `add-initiatives-wiki-validation` : []\n10. `add-audit-log-and-event-history` : []\n11. `add-wiki-bidirectional-links` : []\n12. `add-index-sync-and-consistency` : []\n13. `consolidate-docs-superpowers` : [`developer/agent-implementation-guide`]\n14. `add-mdocs-cli-commands` : []\n15. `add-checkable-plan-items` : []\n16. `add-initiative-priorities-and-dependencies` : []\n17. `add-wiki-stub-generation` : []\n18. `add-wiki-manager-crud` : []\n19. `fix-mdocs-status-error` : []\n20. `fix-mdocs-permissions` : []\n21. `prepare-v1-release` : []\n22. `auto-register-agent-and-skills` : []\n23. `prepare-v1-2-0-release` : [`testing/new-features-playbook`, `release/v1-2-0-readiness`]\n24. `fix-v1-opencode-compatibility` : []\n25. `mdocs-autonomy` : []\n26. `add-mdocs-dispatch-tool` : []\n\n### 5 wiki entries missing backlinks (the linter expects the wiki's `related_initiatives` to include these initiative ids)\n- `developer/agent-implementation-guide` ← add `consolidate-docs-superpowers`\n- `architecture/implementation-plan` ← add `align-implementation-with-philosophy`\n- `architecture/plugin-design-spec` ← add `align-implementation-with-philosophy`\n- `philosophy/origin-narrative` ← add `align-implementation-with-philosophy`\n- `philosophy/core-principles` ← add `define-v2-memory-metadata`, `add-cross-link-graph-linter`, `upgrade-dispatch-memory-retrieval`, `add-resume-status-cockpit`, `align-implementation-with-philosophy`\n\n### 10 orphan wiki entries (need at least one initiative to reference them)\n- `developer/agent-implementation-guide` — referenced by `consolidate-docs-superpowers` after fix in group B\n- `developer/opencode-custom-tool-result-contract` — referenced by `fix-mdocs-first-activation-hook-error`\n- `roadmap/philosophy-alignment-roadmap` — referenced by `align-implementation-with-philosophy`\n- `decisions/opencode-tool-registration` — referenced by `fix-mdocs-status-error`  \n- `architecture/implementation-plan` — referenced by `align-implementation-with-philosophy` (in group B)\n- `architecture/plugin-design-spec` — referenced by `align-implementation-with-philosophy` (in group B)\n- `architecture/philosophy-implementation-gap-analysis` — already referenced by `align-implementation-with-philosophy` etc.\n- `architecture/mdocs-tool-gates` — referenced by `mdocs-autonomy`\n- `philosophy/origin-narrative` — referenced by `align-implementation-with-philosophy` (in group B)\n- `philosophy/core-principles` — referenced by `align-implementation-with-philosophy` (in group B)\n\nNOTE: many of these overlap with group A and group B. After group A and B are applied, the orphan warnings will largely resolve automatically because:\n- Group A links done initiatives to stable wiki refs (which often resolves the orphan)\n- Group B adds the initiative to `related_initiatives` of those wiki entries (which is a stronger form of reference)\n\nBut the linter's \"orphan\" check is based on `related_wiki` (initiative → wiki), not `related_initiatives` (wiki → initiative). So we still need each orphan wiki entry to be referenced by some initiative's `related_wiki`. Use the mappings above.\n\n## Recommended Strategy\n1. **Group B first** (cheapest, fixes 5 warnings + resolves some orphan warnings): edit the frontmatter of those 5 wiki files to add the listed initiative ids to `related_initiatives`. Also add `lifecycle: stable` to each (after promoting them to stable, they qualify as stable learnings, which helps other done initiatives reference them as stable).\n2. **Group A**: For each done initiative, add at least one stable wiki slug to its `related_wiki`. Semantically map initiatives:\n   - `complete-mdocs-cli-commands`, `add-mdocs-cli-commands`, `add-wiki-manager-crud`, `add-wiki-stub-generation`, `add-wiki-bidirectional-links`, `add-index-sync-and-consistency`, `add-initiatives-wiki-validation`, `add-cross-link-graph-linter`, `add-mdocs-linter-for-handoff-quality`, `add-checkable-plan-items`, `add-initiative-priorities-and-dependencies` → all about the mdocs plugin/CLI features. Reference `architecture/mdocs-tool-gates` (after promoting) AND `architecture/philosophy-implementation-gap-analysis`.\n   - `install-mdocs` → `architecture/implementation-plan` (after promoting) and/or `architecture/plugin-design-spec`.\n   - `remove-default-model` → small config tweak. Reference `architecture/mdocs-tool-gates` (workflow design knowledge) or `decisions/opencode-tool-registration` (decisions/knowledge).\n   - `fix-frontmatter-type-mismatch` → `decisions/opencode-tool-registration` (decisions/contract knowledge).\n   - `fix-slug-initiative-ux` → `developer/agent-implementation-guide` (after promoting).\n   - `add-full-text-search`, `add-audit-log-and-event-history`, `add-mdocs-dispatch-tool`, `auto-register-agent-and-skills` → reference `architecture/mdocs-tool-gates` (general architectural knowledge) or `architecture/philosophy-implementation-gap-analysis`.\n   - `fix-local-dogfooding-agent-discovery` → `architecture/plugin-design-spec` (after promoting).\n   - `fix-mdocs-status-error` → `decisions/opencode-tool-registration` (which documents the fix).\n   - `fix-mdocs-permissions` → `architecture/mdocs-tool-gates` (workflow knowledge) or `decisions/opencode-tool-registration`.\n   - `mdocs-autonomy` → `architecture/mdocs-tool-gates` (this wiki entry directly describes mdocs autonomy).\n   - `fix-v1-opencode-compatibility` → `architecture/plugin-design-spec` (after promoting) or `architecture/mdocs-tool-gates`.\n   - `prepare-v1-release` → `architecture/implementation-plan` (after promoting) or `architecture/philosophy-implementation-gap-analysis`.\n   - `prepare-v1-2-0-release` → already references stable entries, but those are `testing/new-features-playbook` and `release/v1-2-0-readiness` (release/v1-2-0-readiness has lifecycle: stable already, so this should be fine). Verify by reading release/v1-2-0-readiness.md lifecycle.\n3. **Group C**: After group A and B, run mdocs_validate and check remaining orphan warnings. For any remaining orphan wiki entries, find the most natural initiative to reference it from and add to `related_wiki`.\n4. Run `mdocs_validate` after each group. The final state must show zero graph warnings.\n5. Run `npm test` and `npm run build` to confirm no regressions.\n\n## Tools to use\n- Use the `mdocs` tool to update initiatives: `mdocs({ command: 'initiative.update', args: { id: '<id>', updates: { related_wiki: ['<cat>/<id>', ...] }, progressNote: '...' } })`\n- For wiki entries, use the `edit` tool to modify frontmatter directly. After all edits, run `mdocs({ command: 'index.sync', args: {} })` to regenerate indices.\n- Read files using the `read` tool, not `cat`.\n- Don't use `mdocs` tool for frontmatter edits on wiki files — use the `edit` tool directly so you have full control over the YAML.\n\n## Specific Wiki Entry Edits Required\nFor each of the 5 wiki entries, edit the `related_initiatives` array to add the listed initiative ids. Also add `lifecycle: stable` to:\n- `architecture/implementation-plan` \n- `architecture/plugin-design-spec`\n- `architecture/mdocs-tool-gates`\n- `decisions/opencode-tool-registration`\n- `developer/agent-implementation-guide`\n- `philosophy/origin-narrative`\n- `philosophy/core-principles`\n\nFor these, also add the v2 metadata fields where reasonable: `knowledge_type`, `confidence`. Look at `architecture/philosophy-implementation-gap-analysis.md` for the v2 format example.\n\n## Process (TDD-style: verify after each batch)\n1. First, read all the relevant files to confirm your assumptions (read at least the frontmatter of all 26 done initiatives and all 13 wiki files).\n2. Apply Group B (wiki entry frontmatter edits).\n3. Apply Group A (initiative updates via mdocs tool).\n4. Run mdocs_validate and check for any remaining warnings. Address Group C.\n5. Run `npm test` and `npm run build`. Both must pass.\n6. Update the initiative's progress log via `mdocs({ command: 'initiative.update', args: { id: 'clean-up-graph-warnings', progressNote: '...' } })`.\n7. Mark the initiative done via `mdocs({ command: 'initiative.done', args: { id: 'clean-up-graph-warnings' } })`.\n\n## Acceptance Criteria\n- `mdocs_validate` returns zero graph warnings (no \"Done initiative has no stable wiki learning\", no \"Wiki missing backlink\", no \"Wiki not referenced by any initiative\").\n- `npm test` passes with no test failures.\n- `npm run build` succeeds.\n- Initiative `clean-up-graph-warnings` is marked done with a progress log summarizing the changes.\n\n## Important Constraints\n- Do NOT modify `src/linter.ts`, `src/__tests__/linter.test.ts`, or any TypeScript code. Only edit markdown.\n- Do NOT delete or rename any files.\n- Preserve all existing semantic content in wiki entries and initiatives.\n- Use single-quote YAML values consistently (match the existing style in the repo).\n- If you encounter any ambiguity or unexpected warnings, stop and report back rather than making destructive changes.\n\n## Final Report\nReturn a structured report with:\n- A table of all 26 done initiatives: id → new related_wiki entries added.\n- A table of all 5+ wiki entries: id → new related_initiatives / lifecycle changes.\n- Confirmation of mdocs_validate (zero warnings), npm test (passing), npm run build (success).\n- Any judgment calls or warnings you had to resolve specially.","subagent_type":"general"}}}
