{"timestamp":"2026-06-03T17:51:08.481Z","type":"tool","initiativeId":"add-opencode-mdocs-to-opencode-ecosystem","step":"IDLE","details":{"toolName":"mdocs","args":{"command":"initiative.create","args":{"title":"Evaluate and Merge PR #3: Wiki Orphan Warning Fix","id":"evaluate-pr-3-wiki-orphan-fix","owner":"bbaaxx","tags":{"item":["review","pr-merge","wiki","validation"]},"objective":"Evaluate community PR #3 (https://github.com/bbaaxx/opencode-mdocs/pull/3) from contributor contributor and decide whether to merge it. The PR makes three changes: (1) accepts `sources` as wiki provenance alongside `source_initiatives`, (2) treats six wiki categories as global (repo, system, overview, index, log, glossary) so they don't require initiative backlinks, and (3) keeps orphan warnings for non-global entries that lack provenance or initiative references. Acceptance: code review passes, tests pass locally, `mdocs_validate` reports no new warnings from real content, and the PR is either merged or closed with rationale.","plan":{"item":["Review the diff for correctness, scope, and design alignment with mdocs philosophy","Run `npm test` and `npm run build` on the PR branch to confirm 170+/170+ tests pass and build succeeds","Run `mdocs_validate` on existing mdocs/ content to confirm no real entries regress into false orphan warnings or escape real orphans","Verify the new global-category list matches categories actually used in this repo's wiki/ (repo, system, overview, index, log, glossary) and update the list if a category is missing or over-broad","Check whether `sources` should be promoted into the schema/spec docs (not just README) so future agents know it is first-class","Decide outcome: approve and merge, request changes, or close with rationale","If merging: confirm CI is green, merge via gh (squash or merge commit per repo norm), delete remote branch, update local main, and verify mdocs_validate is still clean","Mark initiative done with a progress-log entry capturing the decision and any follow-up actions"]}}}}}
