{"timestamp":"2026-06-03T17:51:31.677Z","type":"tool","initiativeId":"add-opencode-mdocs-to-opencode-ecosystem","step":"IDLE","details":{"toolName":"mdocs","args":{"command":"initiative.update","args":{"id":"evaluate-pr-3-wiki-orphan-fix","updates":{"related_wiki":{"item":["architecture/mdocs-tool-gates","architecture/philosophy-implementation-gap-analysis","testing/new-features-playbook"]},"plan":"1. Review the diff for correctness, scope, and design alignment with mdocs philosophy (wiki entries are agent-shared memory, not documents that need human owners).\n2. Run `npm test` and `npm run build` on the PR branch to confirm the full suite passes and the build is clean.\n3. Run `mdocs_validate` against this repo's existing mdocs/ content to confirm no real entries regress into false orphan warnings and no real orphans escape detection.\n4. Verify the new global-category list (`repo`, `system`, `overview`, `index`, `log`, `glossary`) matches the categories actually used in this repo's wiki/ tree; update the list if a real category is missing or if the list is over-broad.\n5. Decide outcome: approve and merge, request changes, or close with rationale.\n6. If merging: confirm CI green, merge via `gh pr merge --squash` (or whatever the repo norm is), delete remote branch, update local main, re-run `mdocs_validate`, and mark initiative done."}}}}}
{"timestamp":"2026-06-03T17:59:22.924Z","type":"tool","initiativeId":"add-opencode-mdocs-to-opencode-ecosystem","step":"IDLE","details":{"toolName":"task","args":{"description":"Evaluate PR #3 wiki orphan fix","prompt":"You are evaluating a community PR for the opencode-mdocs repository. This is a code-review pass. Do not modify code; only read, run tests, and report findings.\n\n# Context\n- Repo: `/Users/bbaaxx/AgentsPlayground/opencode-mdocs` (current working directory)\n- PR: https://github.com/bbaaxx/opencode-mdocs/pull/3\n- Branch: `contributor:fix/wiki-orphan-validation` (remote) → local tracking branch to be checked out\n- Author: contributor (Ed Mosqueda)\n- Initiative being executed: `evaluate-pr-3-wiki-orphan-fix` (in mdocs/initiatives/)\n\n# What the PR claims to do\n1. Add `sources` as a wiki provenance field, alongside existing `source_initiatives`\n2. Treat six wiki categories as \"global\" so they don't need initiative backlinks: `repo`, `system`, `overview`, `index`, `log`, `glossary`\n3. Keep orphan warnings for non-global entries that lack either provenance or initiative references\n4. Touches: `src/wiki.ts` (+10/-2), `src/__tests__/wiki.test.ts` (+66), `README.md` (+2)\n\n# Your job — execute these steps in order and report\n\n## Step 1: Read the diff in detail\n- Run `gh pr diff 3` to see the diff\n- Read `src/wiki.ts` around lines 90–110 and 380–400 to understand context of the change\n- Read `src/__tests__/wiki.test.ts` around lines 270–350 to see new tests\n- Report any design issues, edge cases, naming concerns, or philosophical alignment issues\n\n## Step 2: Verify the tests pass on the PR branch\n- Check out the PR branch: `gh pr checkout 3` (or `git fetch origin fix/wiki-orphan-validation && git checkout -b pr-3-review origin/fix/wiki-orphan-validation` if that fails)\n- Run `npm install` if node_modules is missing\n- Run `npm test` and report the result (test count, pass/fail, any warnings)\n- Run `npm run build` and report the result\n- If any test fails, paste the failure output\n\n## Step 3: Verify mdocs_validate behavior against real content\n- The current working tree (main) has real wiki content. Use the mdocs_validate custom tool to run validation on main first to establish a baseline.\n- Then check out the PR branch's wiki.ts (or simulate by reading the new logic) and reason about which existing wiki/ entries would have their orphan-warning status change. Walk the wiki/ directory and categorize each entry by category. For each non-`initiative` category, list which entries exist and whether the new global-category exemption would silence a real orphan. Flag any cases where the new logic might hide a real orphan (e.g., is there a `system/` entry that legitimately should be linked to an initiative but currently isn't?).\n- Compare the list of categories actually used in `mdocs/wiki/` against the PR's hard-coded list: `repo`, `system`, `overview`, `index`, `log`, `glossary`. Report any used category that is NOT in the PR's list, and any PR-list category that is NOT used.\n\n## Step 4: Assess documentation completeness\n- The PR adds one README sentence. Check whether `sources` should also be added to:\n  - The wiki-entry schema documentation in `mdocs/wiki/architecture/mdocs-tool-gates` (or wherever the schema is documented)\n  - Any in-repo spec or contributing guide\n  - A frontmatter example\n- Report whether the README-only change is sufficient or under-documented\n\n## Step 5: Verdict\nProvide a clear verdict in this exact format:\n- **Verdict**: APPROVE / REQUEST CHANGES / REJECT\n- **Confidence**: high / medium / low\n- **Reasoning** (2–4 sentences)\n- **Required changes before merge** (bullet list, empty if APPROVE)\n- **Suggested follow-ups post-merge** (bullet list, can be empty)\n- **Risk assessment**: any regression risk for users with existing wiki content\n\n## Constraints\n- Do NOT merge the PR. Do NOT push branches. Do NOT modify any source files.\n- Do NOT install anything beyond `npm install` if needed for tests.\n- Stay in the repo; do not clone elsewhere.\n- All commands run from `/Users/bbaaxx/AgentsPlayground/opencode-mdocs`.\n- Return your final report as a single structured markdown block matching the Step 5 format. Include raw output snippets where useful (test counts, category list, etc.).","subagent_type":"general"}}}
