{"timestamp":"2026-06-03T18:01:17.688Z","type":"tool","initiativeId":"add-opencode-mdocs-to-opencode-ecosystem","step":"IDLE","details":{"toolName":"mdocs","args":{"command":"initiative.update","args":{"id":"evaluate-pr-3-wiki-orphan-fix","progressNote":"## Evaluation findings (2026-06-03)\n\n### Verification results\n- **Tests**: 11/11 suites pass, **170/170 tests pass** on the PR branch (was 167 before; the 3 new tests all pass)\n- **Build**: `npm run build` succeeds cleanly\n- **`mdocs_validate` on main baseline**: 0 errors, 0 warnings — repo is already clean\n\n### Critical issue: category list mismatch\nThe PR hard-codes a `globalCategories` set: `repo`, `system`, `overview`, `index`, `log`, `glossary`.\n\nThe actual `mdocs/wiki/` subdirectories in this repo are: `architecture`, `decisions`, `developer`, `philosophy`, `release`, `research`, `roadmap`, `testing` (8 categories, 23 entries).\n\n**There is zero overlap.** The exemption is a complete no-op for this codebase — it never silences a real warning and never hides a real orphan.\n\n### What the PR actually solves\n- `sources` field fallback: minor, backward-compat improvement. Useful if a future agent writes `sources` instead of `source_initiatives`, but `source_initiatives` already works correctly.\n- \"Global categories\" exemption: targets a wiki taxonomy that doesn't exist in this repo. Looks like the contributor assumed a different category scheme (likely from a generic wiki template).\n\n### Verdict\n**REQUEST CHANGES** (do not merge as-is). The exemption logic is well-intentioned but miscalibrated. Two reasonable redesigns:\n1. **Per-entry flag**: add a `global: true` (or `lifecycle: stable`) frontmatter field on wiki entries that should not require initiative backlinks. This matches the precedent set by the `clean-up-graph-warnings` initiative, which already uses `lifecycle: stable` for exempt entries.\n2. **Configuration-driven list**: load the global categories from a config file or from wiki entries' own frontmatter, not from a hard-coded set in source.\n\nRecommend posting a polite review comment with these options, and asking the contributor to either (a) redesign per option 1, or (b) demonstrate a real `mdocs_validate` warning the PR would silence in this repo. If the contributor cannot, the PR can be closed.\n\n### Status\nAwaiting user decision on next step: (A) request changes via PR review comment, (B) close PR with rationale, (C) merge despite mismatch (not recommended)."}}}}
