{"timestamp":"2026-06-03T18:04:43.933Z","type":"tool","initiativeId":"add-opencode-mdocs-to-opencode-ecosystem","step":"IDLE","details":{"toolName":"bash","args":{"command":"cat <<'EOF' > /tmp/pr3-review-comment.md\nThanks for the contribution! Tests pass cleanly and the `sources` fallback is a nice backward-compat addition. I want to flag one structural concern with the global-category exemption before we can merge.\n\n## The hard-coded category list doesn't match this repo\n\nThe PR hard-codes:\n\n```ts\nconst globalCategories = new Set(['repo', 'system', 'overview', 'index', 'log', 'glossary']);\n```\n\nBut the actual `mdocs/wiki/` subdirectories in this repo are: `architecture`, `decisions`, `developer`, `philosophy`, `release`, `research`, `roadmap`, `testing` — **zero overlap** with the list above. The exemption is a complete no-op here, so it would never silence a real warning and never hide a real orphan. On top of that, `mdocs_validate` on `main` already reports 0 warnings, 0 errors, so the orphan detection isn't currently a problem in this codebase.\n\nI suspect the category names came from a different wiki taxonomy (generic / template wiki?). For this repo specifically we need a different mechanism.\n\n## Suggested redesign: reuse `lifecycle: stable`\n\nWe already have a first-class `lifecycle` field on wiki entries with the semantic \"this is settled knowledge, it stands on its own.\" The linter already uses it to identify stable learnings (see `src/linter.ts:127-134`). Exempting `lifecycle: stable` entries from orphan warnings fits that semantic naturally and avoids hard-coding any category list.\n\nSketch:\n\n```ts\n// src/wiki.ts, in the validate() orphan check\nconst isStable = entry.lifecycle === 'stable';\nif (\n  entry.id && entry.category &&\n  !globalCategories.has(entry.category) &&\n  !isStable &&\n  !hasSourceInitiatives &&\n  !hasRelatedInitiatives &&\n  !isReferencedByInitiative\n) {\n  warnings.push(`${relativeName} is not referenced by any initiative`);\n}\n```\n\nThe hard-coded `globalCategories` set can then be dropped entirely (or kept as a future opt-in if you have a concrete use case for it — but please name categories that actually exist in this repo).\n\nA test like the first new one would still be valuable, but rewritten to use `lifecycle: 'stable'` instead of `category: 'repo'`.\n\n## Optional second change\n\nThe `sources` fallback is fine, but if you want to keep it, consider also documenting `sources` in `mdocs/wiki/architecture/mdocs-tool-gates` (where the wiki frontmatter schema lives) — README-only docs tend to drift from the schema.\n\nHappy to iterate on this. If you'd rather close the PR and have me land an equivalent change myself, that's also fine — let me know.\nEOF\nwc -l /tmp/pr3-review-comment.md","description":"Draft the PR review comment"}}}
