{"timestamp":"2026-06-03T18:47:40.983Z","type":"tool","initiativeId":"add-opencode-mdocs-to-opencode-ecosystem","step":"IDLE","details":{"toolName":"bash","args":{"command":"echo \"=== Option A: minimal (checker-only) ===\" && echo \"  - checkConsistency reads each file's frontmatter (id + title)\" && echo \"  - Accept an INDEX entry as matching if it normalizes to: filename, id, or title\" && echo \"  - INDEX format stays plain '- Title'\" && echo \"  - Diff: 1 file, ~15 lines (checker only)\" && echo \"  - Pros: minimal blast radius, doesn't touch the user-visible INDEX format\" && echo \"  - Cons: INDEX entries remain unlinked plain text\" && echo \"\" && echo \"=== Option B: linked INDEX (writer + checker) ===\" && echo \"  - updateIndices() writes '- [Title](id.md)' to match the root wiki INDEX style\" && echo \"  - checkConsistency extracts the link target as the canonical id\" && echo \"  - Diff: 1 file, ~20 lines, regenerates 9 INDEX files on next sync\" && echo \"  - Pros: human-readable, linkable, unambiguous single source of truth (the id)\" && echo \"  - Cons: regenerates the wiki INDEX files in the next sync, which is a visible change\"","description":"Summarize the two fix options"}}}
