{"timestamp":"2026-06-03T18:59:26.314Z","type":"tool","initiativeId":"add-opencode-mdocs-to-opencode-ecosystem","step":"IDLE","details":{"toolName":"bash","args":{"command":"git add mdocs/initiatives/INDEX.md mdocs/initiatives/fix-wiki-index-consistency-check--2026-06-03.md mdocs/wiki/ mdocs/initiatives/INDEX.md src/wiki.ts src/__tests__/wiki.test.ts && git status --short","description":"Stage all changes"}}}
{"timestamp":"2026-06-03T18:59:36.672Z","type":"tool","initiativeId":"add-opencode-mdocs-to-opencode-ecosystem","step":"IDLE","details":{"toolName":"bash","args":{"command":"git commit -m \"fix: wiki INDEX entries use linked format and consistency check matches by id/title aliases\n\nThe checkConsistency() extractor in WikiManager previously parsed INDEX\nlines as plain title text and compared the slug against filenames. It\nnever read each file's id or title frontmatter, so every entry whose\ntitle-derived slug differed from its filename (e.g. id=implementation-plan\nwith title='Original Implementation Plan' and filename=implementation-plan.md)\nwas wrongly reported as both missing and orphan — 12 false-positive pairs\nin this repo.\n\nTwo changes:\n\n1. updateIndices() now writes per-category entries as\n   '- [Title](id.md)' (matches the root wiki INDEX style). The id is read\n   from each file's frontmatter and falls back to the filename when the\n   id is missing.\n\n2. checkConsistency() now extracts the link target as the canonical id,\n   and for each on-disk file builds an alias set from {filename, frontmatter\n   id, normalized frontmatter title}. A file is consistent if any of its\n   aliases appears in the INDEX; an INDEX entry is consistent if some\n   file's aliases match it. Legacy plain '- Title' lines are still accepted\n   as a fallback.\n\nTests (177/177 pass, was 173): cover linked-format writing, file with\nid != filename, INDEX entry matched only by frontmatter title, and\nregression guard that a true orphan (no matching alias) is still detected.\n\nAfter regenerating the wiki INDEX files in the new format and rebuilding\ndist, checkConsistency() on this repo returns consistent: true with 0\nmissing, 0 orphans, 0 stale.\" 2>&1 | tail -5 && git log --oneline -3","description":"Commit the fix"}}}
{"timestamp":"2026-06-03T18:59:50.744Z","type":"tool","initiativeId":"add-opencode-mdocs-to-opencode-ecosystem","step":"IDLE","details":{"toolName":"mdocs","args":{"command":"initiative.update","args":{"id":"fix-wiki-index-consistency-check","progressNote":"### Outcome (2026-06-03)\n\nImplemented Option B (linked INDEX). Two changes in `src/wiki.ts`:\n\n1. **`updateIndices()`**: per-category INDEX entries now write as `- [Title](id.md)`, matching the root wiki INDEX style. The id is read from each file's frontmatter and falls back to the filename.\n\n2. **`checkConsistency()`**: extracts the link target as the canonical id, and for each on-disk file builds an alias set from `{filename, frontmatter id, normalized frontmatter title}`. A file is consistent if any alias appears in the INDEX; an INDEX entry is consistent if some file's aliases match it. Legacy plain `- Title` lines are still accepted as a fallback.\n\n### Verification\n\n- `npm test`: 11/11 suites, **177/177 tests pass** (was 173; +4 new tests covering linked format, id != filename, title-only match, and orphan regression guard).\n- `npm run build`: clean.\n- `node -e \"...new WikiManager('./mdocs').checkConsistency()\"`: **`{ consistent: true, missing: [], orphans: [], stale: false }`** on the current repo.\n- `node -e \"...new WikiManager('./mdocs').validate()\"`: 0 warnings, 0 errors.\n\n### Important caveat about the running opencode session\n\nThe mdocs tool is loaded once when opencode starts and uses the compiled `dist/` snapshot from that moment. The fix and the regenerated linked-format INDEX files are both on disk now, but the in-memory `mdocs_index_check` and `mdocs_index.sync` calls in this session still use the OLD compiled `checkConsistency` and the OLD `updateIndices`. After the next opencode restart (or reload of the plugin), `mdocs_index_check` will report clean and the new linked INDEX format will be the canonical representation.\n\nFor now (during this session), if you run `mdocs_index_check` you'll see garbled output like `wiki/architecture/[original-implementation-plan](implementation-plan.md).md` — that's the old checker trying to parse the new format. Ignore those reports until restart; the on-disk fix is correct (verified via `node` direct call against the fresh `dist/`).\n\n### Status\nCommitted as `5aaab77` on main, ready to push."}}}}
