{"timestamp":"2026-06-03T19:43:54.468Z","type":"tool","initiativeId":"prepare-v1-3-0-release","step":"IDLE","details":{"toolName":"apply_patch","args":{"patchText":"*** Begin Patch\n*** Update File: /Users/bbaaxx/AgentsPlayground/opencode-mdocs/src/index.ts\n@@\n-import { createPlugin } from './plugin';\n+import { createPlugin } from './plugin';\n@@\n export default (async ({ client, project, directory }: { client: any; project: any; directory: string }) => {\n   return wrapToolResults(createPlugin(directory));\n }) satisfies any;\n-\n-export { createPlugin, type MdocsPluginOptions } from './plugin';\n-export { WikiManager, type WikiManagerOptions } from './wiki';\n-\n-// opencode's plugin loader imports a plugin module and attempts to execute\n-// callable enumerable exports as plugins. Keep public API exports available for\n-// consumers (`require('opencode-mdocs').WikiManager`) but make them\n-// non-enumerable so `plugin: [\"opencode-mdocs\"]` remains backward compatible.\n-for (const key of ['createPlugin', 'WikiManager']) {\n-  const descriptor = Object.getOwnPropertyDescriptor(exports, key);\n-  if (descriptor) {\n-    Object.defineProperty(exports, key, { ...descriptor, enumerable: false });\n-  }\n-}\n*** Add File: /Users/bbaaxx/AgentsPlayground/opencode-mdocs/src/api.ts\n+export { createPlugin, type MdocsPluginOptions } from './plugin';\n+export { WikiManager, type WikiManagerOptions } from './wiki';\n*** Update File: /Users/bbaaxx/AgentsPlayground/opencode-mdocs/src/__tests__/plugin.test.ts\n@@\n import * as path from 'path';\n import * as fs from 'fs';\n import pluginDefault from '../index';\n import * as packageRoot from '../index';\n+import * as apiRoot from '../api';\n import opencodePlugin from '../opencode';\n@@\n-  test('package root keeps public API exports non-enumerable for opencode', () => {\n-    expect((packageRoot as any).createPlugin).toBe(createPlugin);\n-    expect((packageRoot as any).WikiManager).toBeDefined();\n+  test('package root only exposes default plugin for opencode loading', () => {\n     expect(Object.keys(packageRoot)).toEqual(['default']);\n   });\n+\n+  test('public API exports live on api subpath', () => {\n+    expect((apiRoot as any).createPlugin).toBe(createPlugin);\n+    expect((apiRoot as any).WikiManager).toBeDefined();\n+  });\n*** Update File: /Users/bbaaxx/AgentsPlayground/opencode-mdocs/package.json\n@@\n     \"./plugin\": {\n       \"types\": \"./dist/opencode.d.ts\",\n       \"default\": \"./dist/opencode.js\"\n+    },\n+    \"./api\": {\n+      \"types\": \"./dist/api.d.ts\",\n+      \"default\": \"./dist/api.js\"\n     }\n   },\n*** Update File: /Users/bbaaxx/AgentsPlayground/opencode-mdocs/README.md\n@@\n That's it — the plugin auto-registers the agent and skills paths on startup.\n+\n+Programmatic API consumers can import managers from the API subpath:\n+\n+```ts\n+import { createPlugin, WikiManager } from 'opencode-mdocs/api';\n+```\n*** End Patch"}}}
